---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy policy"
  description="How HHZ Respiratory Review handles reader data: privacy-first analytics, no identification cookies, no sale of personal data, and grievance-officer contact per India IT Rules 2021."
>
  <article class="prose">
    <h1>Privacy policy</h1>

    <p class="lead">
      HHZ Respiratory Review is a publication. We keep the data we collect to the minimum
      needed to run the site, respond to reader email, and understand in aggregate what
      content is useful. This page describes what is collected, why, and how to reach us with
      privacy concerns.
    </p>

    <h2>What we collect</h2>

    <h3>Analytics</h3>
    <p>
      We use Google Analytics 4 to understand in aggregate what content is read, from which
      countries, and over what kind of connection. GA4 sets first-party cookies
      (<code>_ga</code> and <code>_ga_&lt;stream-id&gt;</code>) used to distinguish one browser
      session from another. It also records the URL requested, the referrer, an approximate
      geographic region derived from your IP address (the IP itself is truncated by Google
      before storage), the browser and OS family, screen size, and the standard GA4 Enhanced
      Measurement events (page views, scrolls, outbound clicks, file downloads, site-search
      queries). Data is sent to Google's servers and retained per Google's published
      retention window.
    </p>
    <p>
      We do not turn on Google Signals, Google-Ads-linked advertising features, or
      cross-site user-ID stitching. We do not use the data for advertising or remarketing.
      If you want to opt out of GA4 across all sites that use it, install the
      <a href="https://tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout" rel="nofollow noopener">Google Analytics Opt-out Browser Add-on</a>
      or enable your browser's Do Not Track / Global Privacy Control signals (we honour GPC
      for US-CCPA-covered visitors).
    </p>

    <h3>Contact forms and email</h3>
    <p>
      If you write to us (at any of the <code>@homehealthzone.com</code> addresses on our
      <a href="/contact/">contact page</a>) or use a contact form on the site, we retain the
      message and the email address you sent it from so we can reply and, where relevant,
      follow up on corrections or tips. We do not add these addresses to any marketing list.
      We do not send unsolicited email.
    </p>

    <h3>Server logs</h3>
    <p>
      Our hosting provider generates standard web-server access logs (IP address, request
      path, user-agent, response code, timestamp). These are used for security and
      rate-limiting and are retained for 30 days.
    </p>

    <h2>What we do not do</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>We do not run advertising trackers or retargeting pixels on the site.</li>
      <li>
        We do not enable Google Signals, Google Ads linkage, or cross-site user-ID
        stitching in our GA4 property. Analytics are used to measure aggregate content
        performance, not to target you.
      </li>
      <li>
        We do not sell or share personal data with third parties for commercial purposes.
      </li>
      <li>
        We do not build reader profiles, and we do not fingerprint devices.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Your rights</h2>
    <p>
      You can email <a href="mailto:grievance@homehealthzone.com">grievance@homehealthzone.com</a>
      to:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Request a copy of any personal data we hold about you (which, for most readers, is limited to email correspondence if you have written to us).</li>
      <li>Ask us to delete any personal data we hold about you.</li>
      <li>Ask us to correct personal data we hold.</li>
      <li>Raise a concern about how we have handled your data.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      We will respond within the timelines applicable under Indian law and, where stricter,
      under the privacy law of your jurisdiction of residence.
    </p>

    <h2>Third-party embeds</h2>
    <p>
      Our pages do not embed third-party content that would pull a visitor's browser into
      another domain's tracking ecosystem. Where we link to an external site — a
      manufacturer's page, a peer-reviewed paper, a regulatory document — that site's privacy
      policy applies to what happens after you click the link.
    </p>

    <h2>Children</h2>
    <p>
      HHZ Respiratory Review is not directed at children under 13 and we do not knowingly
      collect data from them. If you believe a child has contacted us, email
      <a href="mailto:grievance@homehealthzone.com">grievance@homehealthzone.com</a> and we
      will delete the correspondence.
    </p>

    <h2>Grievance officer</h2>
    <p>
      In accordance with the Information Technology (Intermediary Guidelines and Digital Media
      Ethics Code) Rules, 2021, the grievance officer for HHZ Respiratory Review can be
      contacted at:
    </p>
    <address>
      Grievance Officer, HHZ Respiratory Review<br />
      Email: <a href="mailto:grievance@homehealthzone.com">grievance@homehealthzone.com</a>
    </address>
    <p>
      The grievance officer acknowledges reader grievances within 24 hours and resolves them
      within 15 days, as required by the Rules.
    </p>

    <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
    <p>
      When we update this privacy policy, the effective date at the bottom of the page will
      change and, for material revisions, a visible notice will appear on the page for 30
      days. Historical versions are available on request.
    </p>

    <p><em>Effective date: 24 April 2026</em></p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
